> Sweet and buttery with a touch of heat, our quick and delicious maple-Sriracha sauce elevates juicy pork chops to the next level. Sides of tender roasted carrots seasoned with Korean chili flakes and savory sautéed Brussels sprouts round out this plate that's sure to tantalize your taste buds for a speedy weeknight dinner.

== Chili-Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve any larger carrots lengthwise first).

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Korean Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} (use less if you prefer less heat), and @Salt{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Maple Sriracha Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @Maple Syrup{2%tablespoon}, @Ponzu Sauce{12%milliliters}, and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings).

== Steelhead Trout ==

Pat @Steelhead Trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add trout; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

> Swap in chicken or pork chops for trout. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork until ready.

== Brussels Sprouts ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Shredded Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

== Assembly ==

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add Sriracha mixture; cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} (if sauce seems too thick, stir in water 1 tsp at a time).

Turn off heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice trout crosswise.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing pork!).

Divide trout, carrots, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Spoon sauce over trout and serve.

> Trout is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.